DESCRIPTION:Curious about the role of a photographer in a museum? This month’s Tuesday Tidbits features Saikat Das from our collections team who will be focusing on the importance of digitisation and documentation in preserving our cultural heritage. In this session\, discover why these practices are essential and the challenges and delights of effectively digitising and documenting varied objects in a museum setting.\n\nIf you’re curious about how a museum digitises a 9 foot long textile\, captures the details of a miniature painting or if you’re someone exploring career options in the museum and cultural space\, then this session is perfect for you. \n\nTuesday Tidbits is a series that seeks to support youth in career research/building and acts as a space for networking for young people.
