DESCRIPTION:Join us for the screening of three shorts Raat: Night Time in Small Town India\, Khushi's Roshni and Kya Hai Yeh Samjhauta? Co-created and worked on in The Third Eye's Learning Lab through varied processes\, this screening will be followed by a discussion with The Third Eye Learning Lab team and Hansa Thapliyal.\n\nAbout the films:\n\nRaat (35 min):A documentary exploring the hidden lives and experiences of people in small-town India during the night.\n\nKhushi’s Roshni (7 min): A short film featuring Khushi Bano exploring the complexities of online identity and self-representation among young Muslim women in India.\n\nKyaa hai ye Samjhauta?(Dur. 9 min): A short film exploring women's experiences with domestic violence\, and the choices they make in response to it.\n\nNote: All the films will be in Hindi with English subtitles.\n\nCredits\n\nRaat:\n\nMentor: Ruchika Negi\, Editor: Abhinava Bhattacharyya\, Sound (post production): Abhishek Mathur\, Assistance: Madhuri Adwani\, Producer (for The Learning Lab): Dipta Bhog\, Ruchika Negi\, Producer (for The Third Eye): Shabani Hassanwalia\, Shivam Rastogi\n\nKhushi's Roshni:\n\nMentor: Ruchika Negi\, Editor: Gurleen Grewal\, Producer: The Third Eye’s Learning Lab\n\nKyaa hai ye Samjhauta?:\n\nDirection - Hansa Thapliyal\, Camera - Nebu George and Pankaj Baral\, Sound Design -  Amir Musanna\, Sound Final Mix - Shashank Kothari\, Art Direction - Koshy Brahmatmaj\, Edit - Hansa Thapliyal\, Producer: The Third Eye\n\nImage credits: Still from Kyaa hai ye Samjhauta?/ Coming to terms or\, Making your Terms? By Hansa Thapliyal
